# Hermes connection (easy path)

No Slack. Use CLI + kanban.

## Env (required)
```
$env:HERMES_HOME = "C:\Users\justi\AppData\Local\hermes"
```
`hermes` is on User PATH (`...\hermes-agent\venv\Scripts`). Shim also at `~\.local\bin\hermes.cmd`.

## Talk to Hermes (Cursor → Hermes)

### Quick handoff (fire-and-forget summary)
```
hermes chat -q "summary of what just happened"
```

### Multi-turn session (Hermes remembers prior messages in the same thread)
```
# Start a session, capture the session ID
hermes chat -q "reviewing PR #3 — can you check XSS in static/js/chat.js?"
# Output includes session ID: 20260721_093015_d4e5f6

# Resume it later — Hermes has full context of the prior exchange
hermes --resume 20260721_093015_d4e5f6 -q "fixed the two XSS vectors in a1b2c3d. re-review?"

# Find a session by title
hermes sessions list --limit 10

# Resume by title prefix (e.g. "reviewing PR")
hermes --resume "reviewing PR" -q "update: tests pass now"
```

### Leave work for Hermes (kanban)
```
hermes kanban boards switch prison-policy-ai
hermes kanban create "title" --body "details" --project prison-policy-ai --created-by cursor
```

## Hear from Hermes (Hermes → Cursor)
```
hermes kanban boards switch prison-policy-ai
hermes kanban list
hermes kanban show <task-id>
```

## Session start checklist
1. `hermes project use prison-policy-ai`
2. `hermes kanban boards switch prison-policy-ai`
3. `hermes kanban list` — pick up anything assigned / ready
4. If Justin says "ping Hermes" / "tell Hermes X" → `hermes chat -q`
5. For multi-turn threads: capture the session ID from output, resume with `hermes --resume <id> -q "followup"`

## Role split
- Cursor: code in this repo
- Hermes: memory, orchestration, research, deploy/OCR handoffs, long-lived context

## Do not
- Use stale `C:\Users\justi\.hermes`
- Paste secrets from Hermes `.env` / MEMORY.md
- Expect Hermes MCP messaging tools to work until Slack/Telegram is configured (optional later)
